    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="53"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d53">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Presidential Correspondence, lot 66 D 204,
                        “<persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> Correspondence
                    with <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName>”</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1"
                            type="to">Eisenhower</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d53fn1">According to a memorandum attached to the source
                        text, <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName>’s message to
                        President <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> was
                        delivered to the White House on Sept. 14. The White House staff sent a copy
                        of the message to the Department of State the same day.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-14">September 14,
                            1954</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Friend</hi>: You will have seen the messages which
                        <persName>Anthony</persName> sent <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                        >Foster</persName> last night on his talks in Bonn.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d53fn2">This is a reference to <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1"
                            >Eden</persName>’s letter to <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName> of Sept. 13, <ref target="#pg_1184">p.
                        1184</ref>.</note>
                    <persName>Anthony</persName> found <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1"
                        >Adenauer</persName> in fairly good health and as quick as ever, though aged
                    since their last meeting. <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1">Adenauer</persName>
                    much liked the Brussels Treaty idea which he described as a most happy thought
                    and psychologically valuable as providing a focus for European policies and
                    keeping alive German youth’s faith in the European idea. It was also important
                    he thought to devise means of saving <persName corresp="#p_MENDESFP1"
                        >Mendes-France</persName>’s plight.</p>
                <p>We must now see how the talks in Paris go, but on present form it looks as if
                    there will be plenty to discuss with <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                        >Foster</persName> if, as we hope, he can pay us a visit.</p>
                <p>Kind regards,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Winston</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
